cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - This is the most likely category as the paper deals with the Rijndael Advanced Encryption Standard, which is a cryptographic algorithm. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the structure of the S-Box, which is a key component of the Rijndael algorithm. Information theory deals with the quantification, storage, and communication of information, which is relevant to the study of encryption algorithms. 
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper may involve discussions on the computational complexity of the Rijndael algorithm, which is relevant to this category. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The Rijndael algorithm can be seen as a system that takes in plaintext and outputs ciphertext. The paper may discuss the control aspects of this system, which is relevant to this category. 
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper may discuss the implementation of the Rijndael algorithm in software, which is relevant to this category.
